Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
verifyIsolatedCut(25.10)                              verifyIsolatedCut(25.10)

Name
       verifyIsolatedCut  - Checks cuts in all or specified cut layers against
       the spacing rules set by setIsolatedCutRule

Syntax
       verifyIsolatedCut

       [-help]

       [-area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}]

       [-error <integer>]

       [-layer {<cutLayer_list>}]

       [-maxXY]

       [-report <filename>]

       Checks cuts in all or specified cut layers against  the  spacing  rules
       set  by setIsolatedCutRule. If you use the -area parameter, checks cuts
       within the specified area. Reports violations in the log  file  and  in
       verify.isoVia.rpt or the specified report file.

       Note: Violations can be viewed in the Violation Browser.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each verifyIsolatedCut parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man verifyIsolatedCut

       -area {<x1 y1 x2 y2>}
              Specifies  the  coordinates of the area to verify. If you do not
              specify this parameter, the command checks the whole design. For
              example, verifyIsolatedCut -area {0 0 100 100}.

              Default: Entire area

       -error <integer>
              Specifies the maximum number of errors to report.

              Default: 1000

       -layer {<cutLayer_List>}
              Specifies the cut layers to be checked. If you specify only  one
              layer  name, you do not need the braces around the name. For ex-
              ample, verifyIsolatedCut -layer {Via1 Via2}.

              Default: All cut layers

       -maxXY Specifies that the Square metric should  be  used  for  checking
              isolated cuts. By this metric, another cut should exist within a
              square  window from a certain cut. The size of the square window
              depends on the spacing rules set by setIsolatedCutRule.

              Note: If this parameter is not specified, the  Euclidean  metric
              is used for checking isolated cuts.

       -report <filename>
              Specifies  the report file for the isolated cut violation infor-
              mation.

              Default: verify.isoVia.rpt

Examples
              * The following command checks isolated cuts on all  layers  and
                generates a report file named test.isoCut.rpt:

                verifyIsolatedCut -report test.isoCut.rpt

              * The  following  command  checks  for isolated cuts in the area
                specified and generates a report named verify_isoVia.rpt:

                verifyIsolatedCut -area {0 0 1600 1600}

              *

                The following set of commands check for isolated cuts  on  all
                layers using the Square metric. Any cut that does not have an-
                other  cut  within  a  25um x 25um square window is reported:>
                setIsolatedCutRule -spacing 25> verifyIsolatedCut -maxXY

                In the following pattern, no isolated  cut  violation  is  re-
                ported  as  each cut has one or more cuts within a 25um x 25um
                square window.

